sql:
SELECT vaccination_rate_fully_vaccinated
FROM vaccination_over_time
WHERE doses_administered > 500;

SELECT MAX(vaccination_rate_one_dose) AS max_vaccination_rate
FROM vaccination_data
WHERE demographic_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Beacon of hope' refers to the county with the highest fully vaccinated rate;
- 'Leading the way' implies the county with the top rank in the query;
- 'Black population aged 50 and above' refers to the demographic category with race/ethnicity 'Black' and age group '50+'.

- "First step" refers to people vaccinated with at least one dose;
- "Completed the journey" refers to people fully vaccinated;
- "Extra shield" refers to people vaccinated with at least one booster dose.

- "Top three" refers to the highest ranks (1, 2, and 3) in the ranking system;
- "Leading lights" is a metaphor for the most advanced or influential entities in a particular field, in this case, vaccination rates;
- "Demographic category" includes combinations of race/ethnicity, age group, and gender.

sql:
SELECT 
  CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN report_name = 'Demographic Analysis' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) AS percentage_of_demographic_reports
FROM reports;

external_knowledge:
- "Leading the way in the bloom of vaccination" refers to the highest overall vaccination rates;
- "More than half of the population" refers to vaccination rates greater than 50%;
- "The garden has more than 10 plants to measure from" refers to a demographic vaccination data count greater than 10.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(data_id) 
FROM vaccination_data 
WHERE vaccination_rate_one_dose > (SELECT AVG(vaccination_rate_one_dose) FROM vaccination_data);

external_knowledge:
- "Rank" refers to the position of a county when its vaccination rates are ordered in descending order;
- "Most recent data" means the latest available data entry for each county;
- "Vaccination rate for at least one dose" is the percentage of the population that has received at least one dose of the vaccine.

- "Above average" refers to a rate higher than the mean rate across all counties and demographic groups;
- "Demographic groups" include race/ethnicity and age group;
- "Vaccination rate for one dose" is the percentage of the population that has received at least one dose of the vaccine.
